      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For high-level executives, the key is to look impeccably polished, not trendy. Hair should be neat, conservative, and well-maintained, avoiding anything distracting. Makeup, if worn, should be subtle and professional, designed to enhance features without drawing undue attention. Overall, sharp, high-quality tailoring in muted, classic colors is non-negotiable for projecting unquestionable authority.",
      "source": "target",
